clause43: It is hereby stipulated that if the Lessee defaults in the payment of rent for a period of 5 consecutive months, the Lessor shall have the right, in addition to other rights and remedies available under this Lease Deed and applicable laws, to terminate the lease granted under this Lease Deed at its sole discretion and reclaim possession of the Leased Premises as the complete and absolute owner, irrespective of the time that has passed.
clause44: However, the Lessor must provide written notice to the Lessee of its intention to enforce the penalty specified in clause 4.3. If the Lessee settles the overdue rent within 8 days from the issuance of the notice by the Lessor, the Lessor shall not have the right to enforce the penalty. Conversely, if the Lessee fails to pay the overdue rent within 8 days from the date of the notice issued by the Lessor, the lease shall be deemed automatically terminated, with no further actions required from the Lessor.
mortgageClause19: The Lessor may mortgage or pledge the demised premises only with prior written consent of the Lessee. The Lessee's consent shall not be unreasonably withheld. Any mortgage created by the Lessor shall not affect the Lessee's rights under this Lease Deed.
counterpartsClause30: This Lease Deed may be executed in two or more counterparts, each of which shall be deemed to be an original. All digital signatures must be encrypted and comply with encryption standards specified by both parties. Each party retains the right to verify digital signatures.
